This is an action RPG boss battle. Avoid the enemy's attacks
and attack with the A key. While holding the D key, you can
move with your direction fixed.

If either your stamina or health reaches zero from the
enemy's attacks, you will be defeated. Generally, ranged
attacks reduce health, while contact reduces stamina.

When you come into contact with the enemy, you will be held
and continue to take damage until you succeed at the timing
bar. Let's try out the timing bar.

Stopping on yellow is a success, stopping on red is a
critical. If you stop on yellow, you take damage and are
released; if you stop on red, you take half damage and are
released.

Furthermore, taking damage to your stamina from the enemy
will put you in a [Color_14]state of arousal\C[0], reducing
the number of slashes during your attack. A heart mark will
appear on your status during arousal.

Arousal can be removed by walking around a set number of
steps. It is also removed if you achieve a critical to shake
off the enemy. If possible, aim to stop on red.

Learn the enemy's attack patterns. The enemy's attacks have
patterns. Focus on dodging first to learn them.

Make use of the D key's direction lock. Locking your
direction makes it easier to attack and dodge. Attacking
while moving backward can make the fight easier.

Use healing items and skills. There are no usage limits on
healing items and skills (such as deep breaths). It's
possible to heal and push through aggressively.

Use the Action Easer option. Turning on the Action Easer
from the options will significantly lower the difficulty
level. There are no downsides.
